# archon-tui carryover >=500 lines (phase-3 ratchet; shrinks to zero by TUI-310..329)
# NOTE: app.rs was REMOVED from this allowlist under TUI-310 after its
# event-loop body was extracted into event_loop.rs (1250 -> 493 lines, then
# 485 after TUI-330 moved entry types to events.rs). DO NOT re-add app.rs.
crates/archon-tui/src/markdown.rs
crates/archon-tui/src/output.rs
crates/archon-tui/src/task_dispatch_tests.rs
crates/archon-tui/src/theme.rs
crates/archon-tui/src/vim.rs
# TUI-330 (added): event_loop.rs at ~656 lines is the receiver of the app.rs
# extraction under TUI-310 (app.rs dropped from 1250 -> 493 -> 485). Further
# splitting event_loop.rs would reintroduce a circular dependency with the
# app::App struct it mutates (App has >40 fields that every branch of the
# single TuiEvent match arm touches) and fragment the architectural focal
# point of the loop. Coverage is tracked via the TUI-328 80% coverage
# ratchet.
#
# TUI-331 (tightened justification): Remove this allowlist entry when either:
#   (a) An `App::process_tui_event(&mut self, event: TuiEvent)` method is
#       introduced that moves the match arms from run_inner() onto impl App.
#       TUI-311 tracks the input.rs extraction which is step 1 of path (a).
#   (b) The App struct is decomposed into sub-states (App::Input,
#       App::Thinking, App::Output, App::Overlays) allowing variant-specific
#       helpers to accept a narrower &mut receiver than the current &mut App
#       over 40+ fields.
# Once either (a) or (b) lands, run_inner() can be broken into sub-modules
# grouped by TuiEvent category (agent-output, slash-commands, UI-state,
# permissions, voice), dropping event_loop.rs below 500 lines.
crates/archon-tui/src/event_loop.rs
